**Missing default handling for `toGray` in non-UI grayscale conversion.**

For non-UI indexed conversions, `rgbmap` and `fitCriteria` are populated from preferences if not explicitly set. However, when converting to grayscale without UI, `toGray` remains at its default value (`gen::ToGrayAlgorithm::DEFAULT`).

The `get_gray_func` helper (lines 58-66) only handles `LUMA`, `HSV`, and `HSL`, returning `nullptr` for other values including `DEFAULT`. This may cause unexpected behavior if `cmd::SetPixelFormat` doesn't gracefully handle a `nullptr` gray function.



<details>
<summary>🐛 Proposed fix to add toGray default handling</summary>

```diff
   else if (params().format() == IMAGE_INDEXED) {
     if (!params().rgbmap.isSet())
       params().rgbmap(Preferences::instance().quantization.rgbmapAlgorithm());
     if (!params().fitCriteria.isSet())
       params().fitCriteria(Preferences::instance().quantization.fitCriteria());
   }
+  else if (params().format() == IMAGE_GRAYSCALE) {
+    if (!params().toGray.isSet())
+      params().toGray(gen::ToGrayAlgorithm::LUMA); // Use LUMA as sensible default
+  }
```
</details>

